                    <p>We had a Drupal project, implementing a commerce site for a local store. We use <strong>Drupal Commerce</strong>, as always, for this type of websites. You may see that we have alot of <a href="/drupal-themes/commerce">Drupal Commerce themes</a> on our portfolio.</p>
<p>During the project, there was a minor request from our customer: add the <strong>Continue Shopping</strong> button to the cart. This feature is available on Ubercart, especially for Drupal 6 Ubercart users. Most of ecommerce sites have this feature as well. But it is not built-in with Drupal Commerce.</p>
